en_6252801_0	The Disaster Management Centre says  that close to 150,000 people have been severely affected by the inclement arid weather.
en_6252801_1	The Assistant Director of the Disaster Management Centre Pradeep Kodippili said that the districts of Trincomalee, Polonnaruwa, Ampara, Kurunegala, Monaragala and Hambantota have been affected the most.
en_6252801_2	Meanwhile, at a discussion held on Friday, President Maithripala Sirisena said that solutions must be provided to the issue of scarcity of drinking water, which encompass the entire country.
